=== Precincts ===
* Main shrine - The current shrine building was built in {{ill|lt=1971|Q2475|WD=Q2475|1=1971}} (Showa 44) after being destroyed by a fire on September 29, 1969|Q2485}} (Showa 44). Reconstruction of {{ill|lt=reinforced concrete structure|Q1577013|WD=Q1577013|1=reinforced concrete construction}} on October 3, 2007 {{Sfn|Oyora Shrine 4th seat (shikinaisha)|1977}}. Before it was destroyed by fire, it was built in {{ill|lt=Manji|Q1145295|WD=Q1145295|1=Manji (era)}}2 ({{ill|lt=1659|Q6995|WD=Q6995|1=1659}}) and consisted of the main shrine, the shrine, and the worship hall. It was built |Q210684}} with a {{ill|lt=kara gable|Q977293|WD=Q977293|1=Karahafu}}, and the roof was {{ill|lt=cypress bark|Q90373477|WD=Q90373477|1=cypress bark roof}}. The old shrine building had a south-facing side near the north of the precincts, but during the reconstruction, it was changed to an east-facing side near the west side of the precincts.
* Seiden
* Hall of worship
* Shrine office
* Funeral hall
* South gate* Ryūjii (Ryuujii) - In the southwest corner of the precincts, there is a well called ``Ryuujini'' (Ryuujini), and there used to be a well called ``Niwa'' on the north side of the precincts {{Sfn|Oyira Shrine 4-za (Shikinai Shrine)|1977}}. It is said that a dragon snake living in {{ill|lt=Yorami Pond|Q65248853|WD=Q65248853|1=Yorami Pond}} asked a farmer to remove the iron that had sunk in the pond, and in return, he promised rain if he offered water from the well and prayed. There is a legend that in the past, prayers for rain were actually held during times of drought. On the other hand, the garden can also be seen in the "Settsu Meisho Zue", and the place name of the enshrined area of ​​Oyora Shrine is also derived from this, but it is now buried and only a monument remains.
* Kagura Hall - Enshrined Deity: Obihime Obihime ({{ill|lt=Empress Jingu|Q232803|WD=Q232803|1=Empress Jingū}})
* New Kagura Hall - Enshrined Deity: {{ill|lt=Amenouzume|Q462803|WD=Q462803|lt=Tendenmemei|1=Ame-no-Uzume}}
